# Sidewalk and Refreshments - Inventory System Build Plan
## Developer Checklist

**Project:** Sidewalk Inventory System (Django)
**Location:** Dinagat Island
**Last Updated:** April 19, 2026

> **How to use this checklist:** Work through phases in order. Check off each item as it's completed. Do not proceed to the next phase until all items in the current phase are done.

---

## PHASE 0 - Environment Fix (Do This First!)

> The `ImportError: Couldn't import Django` error must be resolved before anything else.

- [ ] Open terminal in project root (`restaurant_inventory/`)
- [ ] Activate virtual environment:
  - Windows: `.venv\Scripts\activate`
  - Mac/Linux: `source .venv/bin/activate`
- [ ] Confirm Django is installed: `pip show django`
- [ ] If not installed: `pip install django`
- [x] Run check: `python manage.py check` - should return **System check identified no issues**
- [x] Run dev server: `python manage.py runserver` - confirm it starts without errors
- [x] Create a `requirements.txt`: `pip freeze > requirements.txt`

---

## PHASE 1 - Project Structure & Configuration

- [x] Verify `config/settings.py` has correct `INSTALLED_APPS` (includes `inventory`)
- [x] Verify `DATABASES` is configured (SQLite default is fine for MVP)
- [x] Set `DEBUG = True` for development, document plan to set `False` for production
- [x] Set `ALLOWED_HOSTS` appropriately (e.g., `['localhost', '127.0.0.1']`)
- [x] Confirm `urls.py` at project level routes to `inventory` app URLs
- [x] Confirm `inventory/urls.py` exists and has all routes defined
- [x] Confirm `templates/inventory/` folder structure matches Django template loader config
- [x] Run `python manage.py migrate` - all migrations applied cleanly

---

## PHASE 2 - Data Models

- [x] **Category model** - fields: `name`, `slug` (optional), `created_at`
- [x] **InventoryItem model** - fields: `name`, `category (FK)`, `unit`, `quantity`, `reorder_threshold`, `created_at`, `updated_at`
- [x] **StockTransaction model** - fields: `item (FK)`, `transaction_type (in/out)`, `quantity`, `date`, `note`, `created_at`
- [x] **MenuItem model** - fields: `name`, `description`, `price`, `category`, `is_available`, `linked_item (FK nullable)`
- [x] Add `__str__` methods to all models
- [x] Add `is_low_stock` property to `InventoryItem` (returns `True` if `quantity <= reorder_threshold`)
- [x] Create and apply migrations: `python manage.py makemigrations && python manage.py migrate`
- [x] Register all models in `admin.py`
- [x] Seed at least 5 test items via Django admin or fixture

---

## PHASE 3 - Authentication

- [x] Confirm Django's built-in auth is in `INSTALLED_APPS` (`django.contrib.auth`)
- [x] Create login URL: `path('login/', ...)` using `django.contrib.auth.views.LoginView`
- [x] Create logout URL: `path('logout/', ...)` using `django.contrib.auth.views.LogoutView`
- [x] Create `login.html` template (styled to match site)
- [x] Add `@login_required` decorator to all inventory/dashboard views
- [x] Set `LOGIN_URL` in `settings.py` to `/login/`
- [x] Set `LOGIN_REDIRECT_URL` to `/dashboard/`
- [x] Create superuser: `python manage.py createsuperuser`
- [x] Test: unauthenticated visit to `/dashboard/` redirects to `/login/`
- [x] Test: successful login redirects to `/dashboard/`
- [x] Test: logout redirects to `/login/` or home

---

## PHASE 4 - Category Management

- [x] `CategoryListView` - list all categories
- [x] `CategoryCreateView` - form to add new category
- [x] `CategoryUpdateView` - form to edit category name
- [x] `CategoryDeleteView` - confirm and delete (block if items are linked)
- [x] URL routes wired for all category views
- [x] Templates created for list, create, update, delete
- [x] Navigation link to categories in sidebar/menu
- [x] Test: create a category -> appears in list
- [x] Test: rename a category -> updates on item views
- [x] Test: delete category with items -> shows error or reassigns items

---

## PHASE 5 - Inventory Item Management

- [x] `InventoryListView` - paginated list, filterable by category, shows low-stock badge
- [x] `InventoryDetailView` - item detail with transaction history
- [x] `InventoryCreateView` - form with all item fields
- [x] `InventoryUpdateView` - edit existing item
- [x] `InventoryDeleteView` - confirm before deleting
- [x] URL routes wired for all item views
- [x] Templates created for all views
- [x] Category filter on list view (dropdown or tab)
- [x] Low-stock badge (e.g., red label) shown on list when `is_low_stock` is `True`
- [x] Test: add item -> appears in list with correct quantity
- [x] Test: edit item -> changes saved correctly
- [x] Test: filter by category -> only correct items shown
- [x] Test: set quantity below threshold -> low-stock badge appears

---

## PHASE 6 - Stock Transaction Recording

- [x] `StockInView` - form to record stock added (item, quantity, date, note)
- [x] `StockOutView` - form to record stock used/removed
- [x] On save: update `InventoryItem.quantity` atomically (use `F()` expressions to avoid race conditions)
- [x] Prevent stock-out that would result in negative quantity - show validation error
- [x] `TransactionHistoryView` - list transactions for a specific item
- [x] URL routes wired
- [x] Templates created
- [x] Test: stock-in increases quantity correctly
- [x] Test: stock-out decreases quantity correctly
- [x] Test: stock-out beyond available quantity is blocked
- [x] Test: transactions appear in history view

---

## PHASE 7 - Dashboard

- [x] `DashboardView` - requires login
- [x] Display: total item count
- [x] Display: count of low-stock items
- [x] Display: list of low-stock items with links to detail view
- [x] Display: last 10 stock transactions (across all items)
- [x] Quick links: Inventory, Menu, Customer View
- [x] Template created: `dashboard.html`
- [x] Test: dashboard loads without errors
- [x] Test: low-stock count matches actual items below threshold
- [x] Test: recent transactions list is accurate

---

## PHASE 8 - Menu Management

- [x] `MenuListView` - admin view of all menu items
- [x] `MenuCreateView` - form to add menu item
- [x] `MenuUpdateView` - edit menu item
- [x] `MenuDeleteView` - confirm delete
- [x] `CustomerMenuView` - public page at `/customer/` (no login required)
- [x] Customer view filterable by category
- [x] URL routes wired (ensure `/customer/` is outside `@login_required`)
- [x] Templates: `menu.html` (admin), `customer_menu.html` (public)
- [x] Test: add menu item -> appears in customer view
- [x] Test: `/customer/` accessible without logging in
- [x] Test: filter by category on customer page works

