## PHASE 9 - UI Polish & Navigation

- [x] Consistent base template (`base.html`) used across all pages
- [x] Navigation sidebar or header with links to: Dashboard, Inventory, Categories, Menu, Customer View, Logout
- [x] Active link highlighted in navigation
- [x] Mobile-friendly layout (basic responsive CSS or Bootstrap)
- [x] Success/error flash messages on all create/update/delete actions
- [x] Confirm modals or confirmation pages for all delete actions
- [x] 404 and 500 error pages customized
- [x] Low-stock items visually distinct (color, icon, or badge)
- [x] Favicon added (fix the 404 error visible in terminal)

---

## PHASE 10 - Testing & QA

- [x] Manual test: full flow - add category -> add item -> add stock -> use stock -> check dashboard
- [x] Manual test: low stock alert fires correctly
- [x] Manual test: customer menu page is accessible without login
- [x] Manual test: all forms show validation errors on bad input
- [x] Manual test: no negative quantities possible
- [x] Check Django system: `python manage.py check --deploy` (review warnings)
- [x] Review all `TODO` and `# FIXME` comments in codebase
- [x] Check for hardcoded secrets in `settings.py` - move to `.env` file
- [x] Confirm `db.sqlite3` is in `.gitignore`
- [x] Confirm `.venv/` is in `.gitignore`

---

## PHASE 11 - Deployment (Local / Network)

- [ ] Decide hosting: local machine, local network, or VPS
- [ ] Set `DEBUG = False` in production settings
- [ ] Set a strong `SECRET_KEY` (use environment variable)
- [ ] Configure `ALLOWED_HOSTS` with actual server IP or domain
- [ ] Run `python manage.py collectstatic` (if serving static files)
- [ ] Set up a process manager (e.g., `gunicorn` + `supervisor`, or just run with `nohup` for simple local deploy)
- [ ] Test production server starts cleanly
- [ ] Set up daily backup of `db.sqlite3` (cron job or manual schedule)
- [ ] Document server start/stop instructions for the owner

---

## PHASE 12 - Handover

- [ ] Write a 1-page owner's guide: how to log in, add stock, record usage, read dashboard
- [ ] Train owner on the system (walkthrough session)
- [ ] Confirm owner can create a backup manually
- [ ] Document how to restart the server if it goes down
- [ ] Leave emergency contact/support instructions

---

## Quick Reference: Common Commands

```bash
# Activate virtual environment
.venv\Scripts\activate          # Windows
source .venv/bin/activate       # Mac/Linux

# Run development server
python manage.py runserver

# Apply database migrations
python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate

# Create admin user
python manage.py createsuperuser

# Check for issues
python manage.py check

# Save dependencies
pip freeze > requirements.txt
```

